    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer134641769" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16474529568396260059">Alexander Berkman was a well known anarchist in the later 19th and early part of the 20th century. He took part in a number of events, including an effort to assassinate a leading industrialist. After years in prison, he continued his activism, editing publications for instance. <br/><br/>This book is an example of his political views. He was hardly the most cerebral and talented of the writers in this movement. But he does address many key questions in his own voice, such as &quot;Is anarchism violence?&quot;; &quot;Wh</span>
  <span id="freeText16474529568396260059" style="display:none">Alexander Berkman was a well known anarchist in the later 19th and early part of the 20th century. He took part in a number of events, including an effort to assassinate a leading industrialist. After years in prison, he continued his activism, editing publications for instance. <br /><br />This book is an example of his political views. He was hardly the most cerebral and talented of the writers in this movement. But he does address many key questions in his own voice, such as "Is anarchism violence?"; "What is anarchism?"; "Is anarchy possible?"; and so on.<br /><br />If you want a brief introduction to Berkman's views, this will suffice nicely. . . .</span>
