<div id="review_3666384643" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3666384643" />
    <a title="Rachel Jackson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18468967-rachel-jackson"><img alt="Rachel Jackson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1581830700p2/18468967.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3666384643?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rachel Jackson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rachel Jackson" href="/user/show/18468967-rachel-jackson">Rachel Jackson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781508705291" href="/book/show/26125910-what-is-communist-anarchism">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3666384643" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12872649764281131459">[Read online: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/alexander-berkman-what-is-communist-anarchism.pdf'>https://theanarchistlibrary.org/libra...</a>]<br/><br/>A very helpful little intro to the ideas and reasoning behind communist anarchism. Alexander Berkman was a well-known anarchist in his day, and clearly went through some ideological challenges and backlash for his beliefs, hence <i>Now and After: The ABC of Anarchism</i>, also called  What Is Communist Anarchism? He lays out the book like a conversation between himself, you, and your friend, the latter of which is skeptical about the idea of anarch</span>
  <span id="freeText12872649764281131459" style="display:none">[Read online: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/alexander-berkman-what-is-communist-anarchism.pdf">https://theanarchistlibrary.org/libra...</a>]<br /><br />A very helpful little intro to the ideas and reasoning behind communist anarchism. Alexander Berkman was a well-known anarchist in his day, and clearly went through some ideological challenges and backlash for his beliefs, hence <i>Now and After: The ABC of Anarchism</i>, also called  What Is Communist Anarchism? He lays out the book like a conversation between himself, you, and your friend, the latter of which is skeptical about the idea of anarchism and influenced by misleading or flat-out wrong ideas of what anarchism is. Because that’s typical, right? Government and capitalism intentionally misleading the public to make everything but themselves sound horrible and evil and terrifying, like they have done to anarchists forever and still do—rather than understanding that anarchism simply seeks to demolish capitalism and idea of class inequality through states, masters and rulers. <br /><br />To realize that this book was published in 1929 and still holds so much relevance today is extremely disappointing. But it proves that Berkman’s (and other anarchists’) ideas are well worth visiting, because we can see that the same inequalities and tensions from nearly a century ago have only escalated and expanded, often under the very protection of the law. Berkman lays out all of these facts of life succinctly and effectively, letting no stone unturned in the capitalist machine as he addresses what the ideal anarchist society would look like. It was simplistic at times, idealistic at others, but as an intro to the subject it was a very helpful refresher on what such a world would look like and what principles people must hold in order to make that world possible.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12872649764281131459" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


