<div id="review_2345303980" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2345303980" />
    <a title="Kelly Innis" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68141752-kelly-innis"><img alt="Kelly Innis" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2345303980?book_show_action=true">Feb 16, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelly Innis" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelly Innis" href="/user/show/68141752-kelly-innis">Kelly Innis</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2345303980" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12792991278467299310">I enjoy the underlying spirit of this book and am fascinated with its ideals of abolishing capitalism and the state. I am not an economist and am not sure about the effects of alternative worker organizations (communes, cooperatives). However, if Berkman&apos;s goal with this book is to give a simple introduction to anarcho-communism, then I think he does a good job. From this book, anarchism is defined as the abolishing of government/State and communism as the shared ownership of the means of produc</span>
  <span id="freeText12792991278467299310" style="display:none">I enjoy the underlying spirit of this book and am fascinated with its ideals of abolishing capitalism and the state. I am not an economist and am not sure about the effects of alternative worker organizations (communes, cooperatives). However, if Berkman's goal with this book is to give a simple introduction to anarcho-communism, then I think he does a good job. From this book, anarchism is defined as the abolishing of government/State and communism as the shared ownership of the means of production and distribution, while communist anarchism is libertarian communism (voluntary communism, abolishing both government and capitalism).</span>
  <a data-text-id="12792991278467299310" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


