  <span id="freeText4172135743619312443" style="display:none">This book often gets low marks. It did even from its author.<br /><br />But I found it an inspiring introduction to Anarchist thought.<br /><br />And this guy is the real thing. He put two bullets into Frick, the steel magnate who killed his striking workers. <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henry_Clay_Frick#Assassination_attempt">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henry_C...</a> Of course, wikipedia blames Berkman for the collapse of the strike. Of course, as it had been, the threat of murder by Pinkertons was the cause of the collapse.<br /><br />An inspiring book. "No by force, not by coercion." One of the Anarchist mottos.</span>
