<span id="freeTextContainer18278637166732595996">The only reason I read this book is to learn more about freedom, and I must admit this book indeed answers quite a lot of questions in my head. If you consider exploring the Bolshevik and much more social revolution topic related, I&apos;d recommend this one. Anarchism is such a complicated topic, but as a dum-dum, I enjoy this book—it&apos;s engaging and easy to digest. <br/><br/>Even so, it was more exciting to google Berkman rather than reading the book itself, lmaooooo. </span>
  <span id="freeText18278637166732595996" style="display:none">The only reason I read this book is to learn more about freedom, and I must admit this book indeed answers quite a lot of questions in my head. If you consider exploring the Bolshevik and much more social revolution topic related, I'd recommend this one. Anarchism is such a complicated topic, but as a dum-dum, I enjoy this book—it's engaging and easy to digest. <br /><br />Even so, it was more exciting to google Berkman rather than reading the book itself, lmaooooo. </span>
